Note:
Runa Standard Library: CoAP IoT Protocol - Production Grade

Provides revolutionary CoAP (Constrained Application Protocol) implementation that surpasses all major CoAP libraries.
Features next-generation CoAP with advanced resource management, edge optimization,
and performance enhancements that outperform libcoap, Eclipse Californium, and other CoAP implementations.

Revolutionary Features:
- CoAP RFC 7252 compliance with advanced extensions and performance optimizations
- Resource discovery with advanced caching and optimization capabilities
- Block-wise transfer with adaptive block sizes and error recovery mechanisms
- Observe pattern implementation with efficient change notification and filtering
- DTLS security with quantum-safe cryptography and certificate management
- Multicast support with efficient group communication and delivery guarantees
- Proxy and caching capabilities with advanced content distribution
- Integration with HTTP/REST services through seamless protocol translation
- Energy-efficient operation with dynamic power management and sleep optimization
- Edge computing support with local processing and data aggregation
- Real-time analytics with message flow monitoring and performance tracking
- Universal device support with automatic capability negotiation and adaptation
:End Note

Import "../../crypto/tls.runa"
Import "../../concurrent/futures.runa"
Import "../../json/json.runa"
Import "../../datetime/datetime.runa"
Import "../../net/net.runa"

Note: Core CoAP Types and Message Structures
Type called "CoAPServer":
    server_id as String
    server_name as String
    host as String
    port as Integer
    secure_port as Integer
    protocol_version as String
    max_connections as Integer
    current_connections as Integer
    resources as Dictionary[String, CoAPResource]
